purposes: it guarantees finite primary\ndecompositions, as well as various finite presentations and resolutions all\nrelated by a syzygy theorem, and the data structures thus produced are\ncomputable in addition to being interpretable. The tameness condition and its\nresulting theory are new even in the finitely generated discrete setting, where\nbeing tame is materially weaker than being noetherian.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 26 Aug 2019 15:45:42 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 12 Aug 2020 02:38:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-08-13"}
